          "name": "Bend in the River",
          "description": "The river narrows and winds around a protrusion of rock that refuses to erode away. You could be wrong, but the rock looks like it might be shaped like someone's face -- perhaps a friend of yours. Squawking birds, buzzing insects and the rotten smell of an age old swamp await you upstream.",
